criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  (a) medical diagnosis of cerebral palsy;

          -  (b) ability to comprehend instructions in a group setting;

          -  (c) no medical procedures involving the lower limbs (including casting and Botox
             injections) during the last six months prior to pre-testing;

          -  (d) able to walk three minutes at a self paced speed;

          -  (e) no seizures during the last year, and (f) functional performance levels between
             II-IV of the gross motor functional classification system (GMFCS)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  (a) GMFCS I or V;

          -  (b) Not being able to comprehend or comply with instructions.
